`load` is now sync.
Also, Jenkins: this is OK to test

Also, regarding the interop test failures: if Protobuf.js is outputting `undefined` values for fields that exist, that is an incorrect implementation of Protobuf 3. Any field not not provided in the serialized format should be deserialized to the default value.

Regarding `undefined`: Default values are on the respective message prototype now, so there shouldn't be any unexpected `undefined`s. This feature requires always using runtime messages (i.e. created from `Type#create`, which the decoder does automatically), because plain objects do not have anything special on their prototypes.

@dcodeIO In GRPC messages are deserialize using asJSON before being passed up to the caller. Iirc there was a option to put the default values on the resultant object. Is that correct? (I'll go check)
@paralin: Yes, "defaults: true".
@murgatroid99 I've added some compatibility fillers to force the `loadObject` output to look the same as before. Let me know what you think.
